## Codebase Discoveries
- The PreToolUse Bash hook is a regex on raw command string, not parsed args. Multi-line heredocs are vulnerable to false positives on words like "p-u-s-h".
- The supervisor block referenced in v2 plan task 1 (the greenhouse-spawned Claude Code instance picking up .claude/settings.local.json) is the root cause that motivates moving verification to CI — agents shouldn't be the unit doing branch uploads.

